I meant that the timer thread could access asyncExceptionHandler variable.
So, if someone later reorders it like this:
StreamTask(){
  this.timerService = new SystemProcessingTimeService(this::handleTimerException, timerThreadFactory);
  this.asyncExceptionHandler = new StreamTaskAsyncExceptionHandler(environment);
}
...
/// schedule task

and removes final from asyncExceptionHandler then timerService thread can see null even after it's assigned.

